    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Books containing the extracts (pericopes) from scripture appointed to be read at public worship; by the 13th century usually incorporated into the missal.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046678/Oxford Dictionary of the Christian Church (1983)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Libros que contienen extractos (pericopes) de las Escrituras destinados a ser leídos en cultos públicos; hacia el siglo XIII generalmente incorporados en el misal.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
